<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=3059#p3059</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=3059#p3059"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Any games out there attempt to write to VROM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=433&amp;p=3059#p3059"><![CDATA[
VROM content: PPU$1234 = #$A5<br />CPU writes PPU$1234 = #$A6<br />CPU reads PPU$1234<br />If it comes back as #$A6 then someone's obviously using VRAM instead of VROM. Authentic games have VROM; therefore someone's using a copier.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Jul 24, 2005 7:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
